Q1- What is Inheritance in java?
-> Inheritance is an OOP concept that allows the subclass to inherit the properties of the superclass.
-> It follows IS A Relationship : Unidirectional - Child class can inherit properties of parent class but not vice versa.
                                : Code reusability
                                : Implementation through extends keyword.

